Parliament, Monday, 6 July 2020 - The National Council of Provinces (NCOP) will tomorrow receive a briefing from the Minister of Human Settlement, Water and Sanitation Ms Lindiwe Sisulu on progress made on measures to provide Water and Sanitation, and address Human Settlements related challenges in response to the Covid-19 Pandemic.
	
	Minister Sisulu’s department plays an important role in preventing the spread of the Coronavirus Disease (COVID-19) through the provision of water and sanitation to enable the upholding of basic hygiene. The Ministerial Briefing will give Permanent Delegates to the NCOP an insight on the direction Human Settlement, Water and Sanitation is heading as far as the fight against COVID-19 is concerned.
	
	Details of the briefing are as follows:
	 Date: Tuesday, 7 July 2020
	Time: 10:00 am
	Venue: Virtual platform
	
	Members of the media who would like to observe the briefing may forward their contact details to Mr Mlindi Mpindi on mmpindi@parliament.gov.za for inclusion in the Parliament Communications Service WhatsApp group, where login details will be shared. Journalists are urged to forward the request using their official email addresses (no private emails).
	
	Members of the public may follow the virtual engagement live on Parliament TV (DSTV Channel 408), via live stream on Parliament YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
	
	Twitter: https://twitter.com/ParliamentofRSA
	
	Facebook: https://facebook.com/ParliamentofRSA
	
	YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/ParliamentofRSA
	
